c. The sounds of the situations Maria finds herself in.","impact":"Catalina Sandino Moreno's performance is extraordinary — interior, watchful, fully inhabited.","overall":"A humanist film in the great tradition. Treats its subject with complete respect."},{"title":"Little Children","director":"Todd Field","year":2006,"rating":8.8,"mood":"dusk","story":"Two unhappily married parents in suburban Massachusetts begin an affair while their community's attention is consumed by a registered sex offender who has returned to the neighborhood.","why":"The compassion fatigue of the caretaker role — the slow death of a life spent caring for everything except the self.","after":"You'll understand why good people do things that look like betrayal.","direction":"Field's narrated film has a literary ambition rare in American cinema — and pulls it off.","cinematography":"Antonio Calvache photographs suburban summer with a photographer's eye for ordinary beauty.","musicSound":"Thomas Newman's score is exactly wrong in the best possible way — ironic domesticity.","impact":"Kate Winslet and Patrick Wilson are both giving the best performances of their careers simultaneously.","overall":"Underrated masterpiece from a director who has still only made three films. Every one essential."},{"title":"A Marriage Story","director":"Ingmar Bergman","year":1973,"rating":9.4,"mood":"ash","story":"Six episodes document a decade of a Swedish couple's marriage, its deterioration, their divorce, and the strange love that persists through the wreckage.","why":"The exhaustion of a relationship that has been carried long past the point either person had anything left — and the love that makes that unbearable.","after":"You'll be more honest with someone you've been managing.","direction":"Bergman directs actors in a register of complete emotional exposure. His best collaborative work.","cinematography":"Sven Nykvist at his most intimate — television close-ups that become an act of courage.","musicSound":"Almost none. The silence is the point.","impact":"Reportedly caused a spike in divorce rates in Sweden. The most honest portrait of marriage ever made.","overall":"A six-hour television miniseries later cut to three hours. Watch both versions."},{"title":"In America","director":"Jim Sheridan","year":2002,"rating":8.7,"mood":"dawn","story":"An Irish immigrant family arrives in New York City carrying the grief of a lost child — and the children's resilience and openness slowly pull the grieving adults back toward life.","why":"The compassion fatigue of grief — and the way children, who don't know to be afraid, can lead adults back from the place loss takes them.","after":"You'll let the people who can reach you, reach you.","direction":"Sheridan directs his own family's story with intimate authority and not a single false note.","cinematography":"Declan Quinn photographs New York's Hell's Kitchen with warm, defiant beauty.","musicSound":"Gavin Friday and Maurice Seezer's Irish-inflected score is grief made into music.","impact":"One of the most emotionally generous films about immigrant survival and family love.","overall":"A small film with a huge heart. One of the great underseen films of the 2000s."}],"label":"10 films — quick browse"}]}],["$","div",null,{"className":"grid grid-cols-2 gap-x-3 gap-y-5 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-4 xl:grid-cols-4 sm:gap-x-5 sm:gap-y-7","children":[["$","$L6","Ordinary People-1980",{"film":"$7"}],["$","$L6","Manchester by the Sea-2016",{"film":"$8"}],["$","$L6","The Farewell-2019",{"film":"$9"}],["$","$L6","Still Alice-2014",{"film":"$a"}],["$","$L6","Wit-2001",{"film":"$b"}],["$","$L6","The Savages-2007",{"film":"$c"}],["$","$L6","Maria Full of Grace-2004",{"film":"$d"}],["$","$L6","Little Children-2006",{"film":"$e"}],["$","$L6","A Marriage Story-1973",{"film":"$f"}],["$","$L6","In America-2002",{"film":"$10"}]]}]]}],["$","section",null,{"className":"py-14 md:py-16 border-t border-line","children":[["$","div",null,{